<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:s="https://admin.wvusports.com/services/xml_schema/story" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/"><channel><title>West Virginia University Athletics</title><link>https://admin.wvusports.com/rss.aspx</link><description>Latest news items for West Virginia University Athletics</description><atom:link href="https://admin.wvusports.com/rss" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml" /><language>en-us</language><ttl>60</ttl><item><title>Mountaineers Advance to College World Series</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/6/baseball-mountaineers-advance-to-college-world-series</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/6/baseball-mountaineers-advance-to-college-world-series</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="The West Virginia Baseball team poses for a photo after winning the NCAA Morgantown Super Regional" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/6/Morgantown_SR_G1_BSB-1230.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – For the first time in program history, the West Virginia University baseball team is going to the Men's College World Series after finishing off a two-game sweep of Cal Poly in the NCAA Super Regionals with a 17-1 victory over the Mustangs on Saturday afternoon at Kendrick Family Ballpark. The Mountaineers improve to 45-15 on the season, setting a new program record for wins.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/6/Morgantown_SR_G1_BSB-1230.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/6/Morgantown_SR_G1_BSB-1230.jpg"><media:title>The West Virginia Baseball team poses for a photo after winning the NCAA Morgantown Super Regional</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/6/Morgantown_SR_G1_BSB-1230.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 6 Jun 2026 20:49:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59172</s:story_id></item><item><title>Eleven CRCA Scholar-Athletes Match Program Record</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/9/rowing-eleven-crca-scholar-athletes-match-program-record</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/9/rowing-eleven-crca-scholar-athletes-match-program-record</guid><category>Rowing</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="A graphic recognizing the 11 rowers named to the CRCA Scholar Athlete team" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/9/ROW26_CRCAScholarAthleteTeam_1920x1080.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – Eleven members of the West Virginia University rowing team were honored by the Collegiate Rowing Coaches Association as 2026 CRCA Scholar-Athletes, including eight with GPAs of 4.0.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/9/ROW26_CRCAScholarAthleteTeam_1920x1080.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/9/ROW26_CRCAScholarAthleteTeam_1920x1080.jpg"><media:title>A graphic recognizing the 11 rowers named to the CRCA Scholar Athlete team</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/9/ROW26_CRCAScholarAthleteTeam_1920x1080.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Tue, 9 Jun 2026 12:11:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>12</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59179</s:story_id></item><item><title>Kelly, Yehl Named NCBWA District 2 Co-Players of the Year</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/8/baseball-kelly-yehl-named-ncbwa-district-2-co-players-of-the-year</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/8/baseball-kelly-yehl-named-ncbwa-district-2-co-players-of-the-year</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Maxx Yehl, Gavin Kelly" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/8/060626_BSB_CalPoly_NCAAT_GB_250_large.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – Sophomore Gavin Kelly and redshirt junior Maxx Yehl have been named the District 2 Co-Players of the Year by the National Collegiate Baseball Writers Association.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/8/060626_BSB_CalPoly_NCAAT_GB_250_large.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/8/060626_BSB_CalPoly_NCAAT_GB_250_large.jpg"><media:title>Maxx Yehl, Gavin Kelly</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/8/060626_BSB_CalPoly_NCAAT_GB_250_large.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Mon, 8 Jun 2026 14:34:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59178</s:story_id></item><item><title>Luck’s Vision Becoming a Reality</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/8/baseball-lucks-vision-becoming-a-reality</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/8/baseball-lucks-vision-becoming-a-reality</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="West Virginia celebrates a run during its 17-1 victory over Cal Poly at Ken Kendrick Family Ballpark on Saturday, June 6, 2026." src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/8/Baseball-Main.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – When Bridgeport's Ben McDougal registered the final out of West Virginia's Super Regional-clinching 17-1 victory over Cal Poly at Kendrick Family Ballpark on Saturday afternoon, there was one man in Colorado sitting in front of his flat-screen television with a mile-high smile on his face.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/8/Baseball-Main.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/8/Baseball-Main.jpg"><media:title>West Virginia celebrates a run during its 17-1 victory over Cal Poly at Ken Kendrick Family Ballpark on Saturday, June 6, 2026.</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/8/Baseball-Main.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Mon, 8 Jun 2026 14:00:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59176</s:story_id></item><item><title>West Virginia to Play Troy in First Game of College World Series</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/8/baseball-west-virginia-to-play-troy-in-first-game-of-college-world-series</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/8/baseball-west-virginia-to-play-troy-in-first-game-of-college-world-series</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Matchup vs. Troy" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/8/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_Troy.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University baseball team will play its first game of the Men's College World Series against Troy on Friday, June 12, at 2 p.m. ET. The game will air on ESPN and WVU will be the designated home team.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/8/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_Troy.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/8/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_Troy.jpg"><media:title>Matchup vs. Troy</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/8/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_Troy.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Mon, 8 Jun 2026 12:21:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59174</s:story_id></item><item><title>Rowing Announces 2025-26 Team Awards</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/8/rowing-announces-2025-26-team-awards</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/8/rowing-announces-2025-26-team-awards</guid><category>Rowing</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="The 2025-26 Rowing Team Awards were announced at the end of the year banquet, including the Senior Oars" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/8/DSC_0292.JPG" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University Rowing program announced its team award winners for the 2025-26 season, recognizing senior award recipients and the Hammer, Flame, Wake and MVP awards winners.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/8/DSC_0292.JPG" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/8/DSC_0292.JPG"><media:title>The 2025-26 Rowing Team Awards were announced at the end of the year banquet, including the Senior Oars</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/8/DSC_0292.JPG" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Mon, 8 Jun 2026 09:27:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>12</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59173</s:story_id></item><item><title>A Statement from WVU Athletics</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/6/general-a-statement-from-wvu-athletics</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/6/general-a-statement-from-wvu-athletics</guid><category>General</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="flying wv" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2023/5/8/flying_wv.png" /><br /><br />During the weather delay at today's NCAA Morgantown Super Regional baseball game, between WVU and Cal Poly, heavy winds blew an event tent over at an adjacent parking lot causing injury.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2023/5/8/flying_wv.png" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2023/5/8/flying_wv.png"><media:title>flying wv</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2023/5/8/flying_wv.png" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 6 Jun 2026 20:15:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>3</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59171</s:story_id></item><item><title>Athletics To Retire Pat White’s No. 5</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/5/football-athletics-to-retire-pat-whites-no-5</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/5/football-athletics-to-retire-pat-whites-no-5</guid><category>Football</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="pat white 5" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/5/1920x1080PatWhite5.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – West Virginia University Vice President and Director of Athletics Wren Baker announced today that the department will retire football legend Pat White's No. 5 this fall at a home game to be determined later this summer.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/5/1920x1080PatWhite5.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/5/1920x1080PatWhite5.jpg"><media:title>pat white 5</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/5/1920x1080PatWhite5.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Fri, 5 Jun 2026 10:27:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>2</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59167</s:story_id></item><item><title>NCAA Super Regional Parking and Tailgating Information</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/3/baseball-ncaa-super-regional-parking-and-tailgating-information</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/3/baseball-ncaa-super-regional-parking-and-tailgating-information</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Tailgating at Kendrick Family Ballpark" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/3/WVU_V_UK_Monday-12.jpeg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – Due to heavy traffic expected in and around Kendrick Family Ballpark, WVU Athletics and West Virginia University are encouraging fans to arrive early ahead of all games in the Morgantown Super Regional.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/3/WVU_V_UK_Monday-12.jpeg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/3/WVU_V_UK_Monday-12.jpeg"><media:title>Tailgating at Kendrick Family Ballpark</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/3/WVU_V_UK_Monday-12.jpeg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Wed, 3 Jun 2026 12:20:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59160</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Take Game One of Super Regionals Against Cal Poly</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/5/baseball-mountaineers-take-game-one-of-super-regionals-against-cal-poly</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/5/baseball-mountaineers-take-game-one-of-super-regionals-against-cal-poly</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Tyrus Hall celebrates after hitting a grand slam against Cal Poly in game one of the NCAA Super Regionals" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/5/EEN00534.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The No. 16 West Virginia University baseball team defeated Cal Poly, 12-2, Friday afternoon at Kendrick Family Ballpark in the NCAA Super Regionals and are now one win away from its first College World Series berth in program history.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/5/EEN00534.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/5/EEN00534.jpg"><media:title>Tyrus Hall celebrates after hitting a grand slam against Cal Poly in game one of the NCAA Super Regionals</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/5/EEN00534.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Fri, 5 Jun 2026 16:33:00 